See, you can have that. That's when I was first 
lieutenant on 21st Company.

41:55.615 --> 42:08.836
See, I'm looking for... That

41:55.615 --> 42:08.836
picture, that's some of the Japanese prisoners.

42:08.856 --> 42:10.018
You see that woman in that room?

42:16.394 --> 42:22.603
This

42:16.394 --> 42:22.603
little one right here? Yeah. Where was this? Mark? 
Mark on it.

42:32.697 --> 42:33.618
Why was she in there? Damn, she was on a troop boat. 
They said she's only true to one. She's true to...

42:39.526 --> 42:44.793
She only serves one Jap and that she's true to him. 
That's what they said. and give a damn.

43:24.535 --> 43:26.637
Well, these prisoners are really well-dressed. 
They look really healthy. You don't want to see

43:29.741 --> 43:34.667
these B-29 pictures because I had to do that only. 
They were all my friends out there. A lot of Aggies

43:39.212 --> 43:42.896
out there. Did you have a lot of Aggies on Guam? Oh, 
yeah, I showed you. Yeah, you showed me them. I gave

43:46.881 --> 43:47.762
you one. You got all those damn people? You got it?

44:00.867 --> 44:02.129
to Admiral Nimitz? Did I? Sure did. I had a personal 
letter from him. Really? Will you tell me about it?

44:07.397 --> 44:12.826
When he dropped back to Pearl, he had me come up and 
thank him. He thanked me personally, but he told me

44:12.846 --> 44:26.267
then that the Code of Military Justice wasn't 
going to work, that the old code we had, rules for

44:12.846 --> 44:26.267
the government of the Navy, did work all through 
the years, what we call rocks and shoals. And he

44:28.576 --> 44:31.019
said the brig was going to be filled up with people. 
Now, I'm licensed to practice for the Court of

44:32.902 --> 44:35.846
Military Appeals over there. See it over there? 
But that's the most useless damn thing in the world

44:38.109 --> 44:43.235
because you can't have office hours without a damn 
lawyer being there. Now, I'm a lawyer myself. Why I

44:47.241 --> 44:56.473
have to stand there and worry about a bachelor who 
needs five days of bread and water with a full

44:47.241 --> 44:56.473
ration on the third day when that's all he could do 
and get it. You understand what you can't do that,

44:56.875 --> 44:59.838
but I'm a lawyer. So if the Admiral Nimitz is right, 
the brig's awful. What have you had? Look how many

45:04.724 --> 45:08.207
desertions you've had in all the services. How 
many BCDs? How many of this, that, and the other?

45:13.133 --> 45:21.382
When you start with that discipline in the squad, 
the corporals say to you, all right, Anderson, you

45:13.133 --> 45:21.382
don't go ashore this weekend. You leave your 
liberty card in the rack. And old Anderson goes to

45:24.706 --> 45:26.848
think, what did I do? What did I do? And he knows what 
he did. And you don't have any problem with

45:31.289 --> 45:35.695
Anderson. Then another guy comes up and he does 
something, and he gives him some EPD, vector

45:35.715 --> 45:43.105
police duty to the sergeant there, or the 
corporal. That straightens him out. That stops

45:46.349 --> 45:47.370
him there. Or if he goes up to the platoon 
commander, he'll give him something that's out on

45:48.151 --> 45:52.277
his record. And he'll discipline then. They were 
founded on that through the years aboard ship

45:55.482 --> 46:01.069
every place, see? And then when it went up to the 
company commander, he'd shake you around. And

46:07.136 --> 46:17.208
then if you had a court martial when it went up to the 
battalion commander, he might find some

46:07.136 --> 46:17.208
extenuating circumstances and he'll cut your 
sentence down and it gets up to the division, he'd

46:07.136 --> 46:17.208
cut it down. And when it finally gets to the JAG 
office, This cut down, that's the court of justice

46:21.284 --> 46:30.353
we've been operating through the years, not 
having a goddamn lawyer sitting

46:21.284 --> 46:30.353
there. I had to go out and be a witness out at the Army 
or at Guam. I thought I was in the courthouse down in

46:33.477 --> 46:36.440
Houston, all the damn lawyers. I said, you son of a 
bitch, why haven't you got a rifle or something?

46:40.884 --> 46:42.626
Why aren't you out fighting? The war is not over 
yet. Oh, I'm a legal officer, legal. Well, what did

46:48.412 --> 46:49.553
you think of Nimitz? He was a great admiral. Great 
man. Did you ever meet Bull Halsey? Yes, I met Bull

46:55.423 --> 46:56.906
Halsey. And what did you think of him? He was a great 
fighting man, too. Forward man. He wasn't as

47:02.515 --> 47:07.183
reserved as Admiral Nimitz was, but he was a good 
fighting man. In fact, Admiral Halsey gave me the

47:08.825 --> 47:12.872
order to prosecute people in Samoa. Anybody.

